    description: 'Complete energy retrofitting and smart illumination for a 2,50,000 sq. ft. warehousing and distribution facility.',
    challenge: 'The facility was operating with outdated metal halide fixtures, yielding poor lux levels (under 80 lux) and experiencing frequent downtime. The client required a maintenance-free system with a minimum average of 150 lux at floor level while reducing energy bills by at least 55%.',
    solution: 'KARVIN conducted an intensive lighting audit and replaced 600 Metal Halide lamps with 380 Hyperion High Bay LEDs. The wider optical design of the Hyperion series allowed a reduction in total fixture count. We also deployed Via Street Lights on the peripheral roads.',
