    client: 'Leela Hotels & Resorts',
    productsUsed: ['Kronos High-Output Flood Light 150W', 'Helios Facade Wall Luminaire 12W', 'Aura Premium Downlight 12W'],
    description: 'Transformative facade lighting and outdoor landscape illumination emphasizing the traditional palace structure.',
    challenge: 'Illuminating a historic heritage building requires deep precision. The lighting system could not alter the external aesthetic, and structural drills were heavily restricted. The lighting color had to match the exact 2700K warmth of traditional lanterns while outputting high-lumen throws to outline architectural peaks.',
    solution: 'We engineered custom brackets and custom warm-white (2700K) optics for Helios wall lights and Kronos floodlights. By projecting grazing light from structural bases, we highlighted the stone textures without drilling into main masonry. The project reduced power consumption for outdoor lighting by 62%.',
